A basic two-parameter engine where RPM is the rotations per minute of the engine and Load is the percentage of load the engine is under, from negative 100% to postitive 100%.
Notice that the samples on the RPM layer use Autopitch, which uses the fundamental frequency of that loop. The transition between on and off load is achieved through automation on a 3-EQ and a Distortion filter.
Recordings by David Nichols of Track Time Audio. Engine is a 1985 Mercedes-Benz 190E-16V.
